Jigawa State Governor Muhammad Badaru has called on the Muslim ummah to imbibe the core values and lessons they have learned during the month of Ramadan including piety, generosity, peaceful coexistence and justice among other. This was contained in a press statement by the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on New Media Auwal D. Sankara (Fica) issued to DAILY POST. He said the lessons learned if put into use would guide relations among human beings for the progress of society. “Let us embrace the spirit of love, tolerance, forgiveness and brotherhood preached by Islam and other religions” “Having observed strictly the injunctions of Almighty Allah through fasting, prayers and by offering Zakat to the less privileged, the lessons learned during the holy month of Ramadan should not be lost,” Governor Badaru said. “I am urging the good people of the State to sustain their prayers for peace and stability in Jigawa State” “As we are approaching the 2023 general Elections I urge politicians and electorates to conduct themselves in a peaceful manner during primaries and general elections”, Badaru said. The Governor, however, congratulated the whole Muslim ummah for the completion of the Holy month of Ramadan, while urging them to observe the Eid-Fitr festival in a peaceful manner.